  "title": "What is the url request to reset react instantsearch hits?",
  "body": "I am using react instantsearch and sometime i need to check if my index has new entries without to be required to remounting my component.\r\n\r\nSo i know that when my component is called the first time, `react-instantsearch` make an initial request to fetch the most pertinent hits :\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n export const Hits = connectInfiniteHits(({ hits, hasMore, refine,currentRefinement}) => {\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nreturn (\r\n\r\n\r\n  <View>//put my Hits here//</View>\r\n\r\n);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo in my case i need to re-fetch hits sometimes but when i call a new instance of `<Hits />`  i get the same result even if my index has new entries. I always need to manually reset my component to see the changes.\r\n\r\nI may have need a simple url to fetch and update my hits, for ex : `axios.get('/getLastHits'....`\r\n\r\nAny idea ?",
